  "script_data": [
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_001",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 0,
        "end_time": 180,
        "duration": 180
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "A confined space thick with denial and fragile memory.\n\nA bare room. One wooden chair. A metal table. A door with peeling paint that looks as though it has been shut for years.\n\nARIN grips the handle, rattling it with restless urgency.\n\nARIN:\nIt was open. I remember the way the air moved through it, the way it didnt resist when I pushed it, the way it felt like there was still somewhere to go. We did not lock it. I would remember locking it. I would remember the sound. I would remember the weight of the key turning. You dont just forget something like that.\n\nHe pulls again, harder, as though force could undo fact.\n\nARIN:\nWe never locked it. Not that day. Not after everything that happened. I wouldnt have done that.\n\nMEERA sits quietly in the chair, composed, watching him with a stillness that feels practiced.\n\nMEERA:\nYou did. You stood exactly where youre standing now. Your hand was shaking, but you still turned the key. You didnt look at me when you did it. You just stared at the door like it was something dangerous.\n\nA faint electrical hum begins to vibrate through the space.\n\nARIN:\nAfraid? Thats what youre going to say next, isnt it? That I was afraid? Afraid of what exactly? Of a door? Of a room? Of you?\n\nMEERA:\nOf remembering.\n\nSilence settles like dust.",
        "word_count": 233,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (00:00 \u2013 03:00)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 2
      },
