    {
      "scene_id": "scene_002",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 180,
        "end_time": 360,
        "duration": 180
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "The air tightens as accusation begins to splinter reality.\n\nARIN begins pacing in restless circles.\n\nARIN:\nYou always speak like youre narrating something thats already finished. Like its written down somewhere and I just havent read the right page yet. But memory doesnt work like that. It shifts. It blurs. It protects you from things youre not ready to carry.\n\nHe drags his hand across the wall flakes of paint fall like ash.\n\nARIN:\nThis place isnt real. None of this is. It feels staged, like something built to trap me inside a version of events that only makes sense to you.\n\nMEERA rises slowly.\n\nMEERA:\nIf it isnt real, then why does it feel heavy in your chest? Why does your breathing change when you look at that door? Why do your hands shake when you pretend not to recognize it?\n\nThe hum deepens, almost imperceptibly.\n\nARIN slams his fist against the wall.\n\nARIN:\nStop twisting it! Stop reshaping things until they fit your narrative. I was there. I stayed. I did everything I could.\n\nMEERA steps closer.\n\nMEERA:\nYou did what you could live with.\n\nA childs faint laugh echoes somewhere unseen.\n\nBoth freeze.",
        "word_count": 196,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (03:00 \u2013 06:00)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 2
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "fear",
        "primary_score": 0.665,
        "secondary_emotion": null,
        "secondary_score": 0,
        "all_scores": {
          "fear": 0.665,
          "anger": 0.181,
          "neutral": 0.091,
