    {
      "scene_id": "scene_003",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 360,
        "end_time": 480,
        "duration": 120
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Innocence intrudes, soft but impossible to ignore.\n\nThe laugh returns, distant yet intimate.\n\nARIN (whispering):\nYou heard that. Tell me you heard that. Because if you didnt, then that means its only in my head, and if its only in my head, then maybe youre right about everything else too.\n\nMEERA:\nI heard it. And you know who it belongs to.\n\nThe laugh shifts into a small cough.\n\nARIN steps back.\n\nARIN:\nNo. Thats not fair. Thats not fair to bring that here. We agreed we wouldnt do this. We agreed we wouldnt dig it up like this.\n\nMEERA:\nYou dont get to choose which parts survive.\n\nThe door handle rattles violently on its own.",
        "word_count": 115,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (06:00 \u2013 08:00)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 2
      },
      "emotion": {
