    {
      "scene_id": "scene_004",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 480,
        "end_time": 630,
        "duration": 150
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "The world opens into something deeper than denial.\n\nThe wall behind the table cracks and splits open, revealing a narrow corridor stretching into darkness.\n\nCold air spills into the room like a held breath released.\n\nARIN:\nThat wasnt there before. I would have seen it. I would have noticed something like that.\n\nMEERA:\nIt has always been there. You just never allowed yourself to walk far enough to find it.\n\nA faint melody hums from within the darkness.\n\nARIN hesitates, then steps forward.\n\nEach footstep echoes too long, as though the corridor remembers more than it shows.",
        "word_count": 97,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (08:00 \u2013 10:30)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 2
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "fear",
        "primary_score": 0.355,
        "secondary_emotion": null,
        "secondary_score": 0,
        "all_scores": {
          "fear": 0.355,
          "surprise": 0.231,
          "neutral": 0.204,
          "disgust": 0.104,
          "sadness": 0.08
        },
        "method": "ml_chunked"
      },
      "doc_type": "theatrical_script"
    },
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_005",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 630,
        "end_time": 750,
        "duration": 120
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Time stretches sound fractures into accusation.\n\nThe corridor feels endless.\n\nARIN:\nHow long does this go on? How far do you expect me to walk before something changes? Before this becomes manageable? Before I wake up?\n\nMEERA:\nAs long as it needs to be. Memory doesnt measure itself in distance.\n\nThe hum returns, layered with static.\n\nTHE VOICE (distorted):\nYou promised.\n\nARIN spins.\n\nARIN:\nStop using that voice. Stop making it sound like that. Thats not how it sounded. Thats not how they said it.\n\nTHE VOICE:\nYou promised.\n\nThe walls pulse faintly.",
        "word_count": 93,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (10:30 \u2013 12:30)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "THE VOICE",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 3
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "neutral",
        "primary_score": 0.671,
        "secondary_emotion": null,
        "secondary_score": 0,
        "all_scores": {
          "neutral": 0.671,
          "anger": 0.126,
          "surprise": 0.071,
