      "doc_type": "theatrical_script"
    },
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_006",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 750,
        "end_time": 960,
        "duration": 210
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Images surface truth refuses distortion.\n\nThe corridor walls flicker with projections.\n\nA hospital hallway.\nRain streaking down glass.\nA small hand gripping ARINs finger.\n\nARIN:\nThats not how it happened. Youre showing it wrong. I didnt leave like that. I didnt walk away. I stayed until they told me to go. I stayed until I couldnt breathe in that room anymore.\n\nMEERA:\nYou left before the end. Thats the part you never let yourself see.\n\nCHILD (offstage, clearer now):\nYou said youd come back.\n\nARIN collapses against the wall.",
        "word_count": 89,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (12:30 \u2013 16:00)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 2
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "anger",
        "primary_score": 0.298,
        "secondary_emotion": "neutral",
        "secondary_score": 0.392,
        "all_scores": {
          "neutral": 0.392,
          "anger": 0.298,
          "surprise": 0.12,
          "fear": 0.084,
          "disgust": 0.069
        },
        "method": "ml_chunked"
      },
      "doc_type": "theatrical_script"
    },
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_007",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 960,
        "end_time": 1110,
        "duration": 150
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Judgment stands silent at the end of the path.\n\nAt the far end stands the OLD MAN, unmoving.\n\nARIN:\nWho are you supposed to be? Another version of me? Another witness? Another accusation?\n\nMEERAs voice softens.\n\nMEERA:\nLook at him.\n\nThe OLD MAN raises his trembling hand. A small brass key rests in his palm.\n\nARIN:\nThats not mine. I never carried that. I never wanted that responsibility.\n\nTHE VOICE:\nYou locked it.\n\nARIN:\nI locked nothing!\n\nThe corridor flickers violently.",
        "word_count": 81,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (16:00 \u2013 18:30)",
        "speakers": [
          "MEERA",
          "THE VOICE",
          "ARIN"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 3
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "fear",
        "primary_score": 0.578,
        "secondary_emotion": "anger",
        "secondary_score": 0.373,
        "all_scores": {
          "fear": 0.578,
          "anger": 0.373,
          "disgust": 0.017,
          "neutral": 0.015,
          "surprise": 0.01
        },
        "method": "ml_chunked"
      },
      "doc_type": "theatrical_script"
    },
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_008",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 1110,
        "end_time": 1230,
        "duration": 120
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Grief finally pierces through defiance.\n\nThe CHILD now stands between ARIN and the OLD MAN.\n\nCHILD:\nWhy didnt you come back?\n\nARINs voice breaks.\n\nARIN:\nI tried. I stood outside the door for hours after. I couldnt face what was inside. I thought if I waited long enough, it would undo itself. I thought if I didnt look at it directly, it wouldnt be final.\n\nCHILD:\nYou left.\n\nMEERA:\nYou chose distance over pain.\n\nARIN screams, the sound stretching endlessly.",
        "word_count": 80,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (18:30 \u2013 20:30)",
        "speakers": [
          "CHILD",
          "ARIN",
          "MEERA"
        ],
        "speaker_count": 3
      },
      "emotion": {
        "primary_emotion": "sadness",
        "primary_score": 0.294,
        "secondary_emotion": null,
        "secondary_score": 0,
        "all_scores": {
          "sadness": 0.294,
          "neutral": 0.28,
          "anger": 0.167,
          "fear": 0.143,
          "disgust": 0.077
        },
        "method": "ml_chunked"
      },
      "doc_type": "theatrical_script"
    },
    {
      "scene_id": "scene_009",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 1230,
        "end_time": 1290,
        "duration": 60
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "Silence returns, heavier but honest.\n\nThe corridor dissolves.\n\nThe room reforms.\n\nOnly ARIN remains.\n\nThe key lies on the table.\n\nHe picks it up slowly.",
        "word_count": 25,
        "type": "timestamped_scene",
        "header": "Scene (20:30 \u2013 21:30)",
        "speakers": [],
        "speaker_count": 0
      },
      "emotion": {
